# {{.ProjectName}}

Claude plugin generated by [plugin-kit-ai](https://github.com/777genius/plugin-kit-ai) `init`.
{{- if .IsCustomLogicTemplate }}

This is the advanced custom-logic path. Choose it when the plugin's value lives in your code, hooks, or runtime behavior instead of only wiring an existing service or local tool.

## What You Edit First

- `plugin/plugin.yaml`: shared plugin identity and target scope
- `plugin/launcher.yaml`: runtime and entrypoint metadata
- `cmd/{{.ProjectName}}/main.go`: the Go runtime logic that defines the plugin behavior
- `plugin/targets/claude/...`: authored Claude hook and packaging state

## What Gets Generated

- managed guidance files at the repo root such as `README.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `AGENTS.md`, and `GENERATED.md`
- native Claude output such as `hooks/hooks.json`

Start with this `plugin/README.md`, then run `plugin-kit-ai inspect . --authoring` before you expand the repo into more outputs.
{{- end }}

## Status

- Runtime: `go`
- Status: `production-ready`, stable default path
- Bootstrap contract: Go `1.22+`

Choose this lane when long-term support, packaged distribution, and the clearest release story matter more than matching an existing interpreted runtime.

## First Run

```bash
go test ./...
go build -o bin/{{.ProjectName}} ./cmd/{{.ProjectName}}
plugin-kit-ai validate . --platform claude --strict
plugin-kit-ai test . --platform claude --all
plugin-kit-ai dev . --platform claude --event Stop
```

The scaffold consumes `github.com/777genius/plugin-kit-ai/sdk@{{.GoSDKVersion}}` as a normal Go module release.

## Stable Default

- `Stop`
- `PreToolUse`
- `UserPromptSubmit`

The scaffold wires only the public-stable Claude hook subset by default.

Use `plugin-kit-ai init <name> --platform claude --claude-extended-hooks` when you intentionally want the full runtime-supported hook set scaffolded.

## Target Files

- `plugin/launcher.yaml`: runtime and entrypoint metadata for the Claude runtime lane
- `plugin/targets/claude/hooks/hooks.json`: authored Claude hook routing
- `hooks/hooks.json`: generated managed Claude hook file
- `fixtures/claude/*.json`: pre-generated stable Claude smoke payloads owned by this project
- `goldens/claude/*`: pre-generated stable stdout/stderr/exit contract owned by this project
- Optional first-class Claude breadth via `--extras`:
  - `plugin/targets/claude/settings.json` -> generated `settings.json`
  - `plugin/targets/claude/lsp.json` -> generated `.lsp.json`
  - `plugin/targets/claude/user-config.json` -> generated `plugin.json.userConfig`
  - `plugin/targets/claude/manifest.extra.json` -> manifest passthrough for non-managed keys only

If you move the project, update the authored hook command paths so they still point at `{{.Entrypoint}}`.
Keep stdout reserved for Claude responses and write diagnostics to stderr only.
